Enum UMLType

java.lang.Object

      de.uni.bamberg.wiai.minf.forflow.datagenerator.controller.UMLType
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<UMLType>
public enum UMLType
extends java.lang.Enum<UMLType>

UMLType defines three types of possible class types. Comparable to a tree in UML models exists an hierarchy.

The top-level classes do not have any base class itself, but hand down it's behaviour to sub-classes. Here we say it's a root. To stick at the tree image.

Classes which inherit from base class and have itself sub-classes are said to be nodes, because they have the job of an intermediate.

The last case is a class, which has a base class, but has itself no sub-class. We say that's a leave.

Classes which have the roll of a leave are the once we're interested in. 'Cos they are concrete specifications to which test data should be generated at the end.

Notice, this enumeration is stored in controller layer and is used only by that. It doesn't reflect the model layer or anything else. It's just used to controller the parsing of EMF Ecore files properly.

ROOT

public static final UMLType ROOT
In UML language a root is a base class. The class itself has no super class, but has one or more subclasses.

A node in UML language has a base class and one or more subclasses.
